text: Will be on @CNNsotu tomorrow to discuss operation against Abu Sayyaf with @brikeilarcnn at 9 am EST/6 am PST and 12 pm EST/9 am PST.
ISIS, like Al Qaeda, has proven adept at replacing its commanders and we will need to keep up the pressure on its leadership and financing.
Sayyaf's loss & other senior leadership is setback to ISIS, but we're under no illusion about long-term impacts of any particular operation.
Operations like this & coalition strikes on ISIS oil infrastructure put increasing pressure on economics undergirding terrorist organization
Willingness to mount an effort to capture Abu Sayyaf underscores importance of cutting off ISIS resources & Admin's determination to do so.
Thanks to brave US personnel who carried out operation against Abu Sayyaf. There are serious risks to our troops with any operation in Syria
Even now, some in the railroad industry & in Congress have been trying to delay implementation of Positive Train Control across the country.
The tragic #Amtrak188 accident this week reminds us again of the terrible price we pay for delay of implementing Positive Train Control.
